-- Raytheon wins U.S. Air Force missile deal
-- 
-- Mon Apr 16, 2007 5:34pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/16/businesspro-raytheon-missile-dc-idUSN1634988320070416

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - Raytheon Co. ( RTN.N ) has won a $180 
million contract to build new updated AIM-120D Advanced 
Medium-Range Air to Air Missiles (AMRAAM) for the U.S. Air 
Force, the Pentagon said on Monday. 

  The contract, which runs through January 2010, includes 
five AIM-120D AMRAAM Air Vehicles Instrumented, 96 AIM-120D 
AMRAAM Air Vehicles, and associated items.  Waltham, Massachusetts-based Raytheon has been working on 
the new "D" version of the AMRAAM missiles, which offers 
greater accuracy and a big increase in range over earlier 
versions.